commit.message: Increment version to 3.0
Move helper function next to macro

Improve KEYS validation logic and error messages

Some error messages should now better point to the root cause.

In addition, the test suite now controls evaluation so as to produce
all errors and warnings at runtime instead of load time.
Update the edebug spec to include characters
Update the README to reflect current supported syntax
Implement support for characters in KEYS

Update the docstring for "with-simulated-input"

It now reflects the currently supported, non-deprecated uses only.

Clean up code for "with-simulated-input" macro

Also improved warning messages a bit.
Skip coverage calculation on older Emacsen
Add debug declarations to macros in test file
Enable undercover on all tested Emacs versions
Be more selective about which file changes trigger a CI run
Cache the return value of wsi-get-unbound-key
Implement warnings for no-op KEYS inside a variable value

Eliminate unnecessary quotes in test suite

Since unquoted lists are now the preferred syntax, the test suite
should reflect that except when it is specifically testing the
deprecated syntax.

Don't use "define-advice" in tests

This macro doesn't exist in Emacs 24.
Implement warnings for inputs that have no effect
Improve code for detecting warnings in tests

Add warnings for quoted list KEYS and nil/constant BODY

The former is deprecated and the latter is a likely the unintended
result of a typo.
Improve error messages for invalid/incomplete KEYS
